{"lemma":"ضامِرٌ","slug":"ضامِرٌ","root":"ض.م.ر","root_slug":"ض-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-م-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضامِر","root":"ضمر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26031"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26031","headword_ar":"ضَامِرٌ","root":"Dmr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lean, and lank in the belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.; see 1;] (A, K;) applied to a he-camel, (K,) and to a horse, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DamorN","text_ar":"ضَمْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDam~arN","text_ar":"مُضَمَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDoTamirN","text_ar":"مُضْطَمِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) and to a she-camel, (S, A, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAmirapN","text_ar":"ضَامِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [and to a man;]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAmirN","text_ar":"ضَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel being regarded as a possessive epithet [signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu DumorK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ ضُمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DamorN","text_ar":"ضَمْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank in the belly, and small and slender in person;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man: (S, A, K:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAmirN","text_ar":"ضَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dum~arN","text_ar":"ضُمَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 473.) ―         -b2-  And A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of preparation for racing, by his having been fed with food barely sufficient to sustain him, after having become fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolN DaAmirapN","text_ar":"خَيْلٌ ضَامِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAmiru","text_ar":"ضَوَامِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses in that state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  Applied to grain, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and to a branch or twig,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sapless; dried up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoDamirN","text_ar":"مُنْضَمِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","TA","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"ضامر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_15","lexicon_en":"Ibn Mālik, al-Alfāẓ al-Mukhtalifa fī l-Maʿānī al-Muʾtalifa (d. 1274 CE)","lexicon_ar":"الألفاظ المختلفة في المعاني المؤتلفة لابن مالك","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22451#43439d","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">بَاب المهزول والضامر</span><br><br><span>نحيف نحيل ضئيل مهزول نضو ناحل منهوك معروق الْعِظَام غث أعجف </span>"}]}}